
ğŸ”° 1. What is Time Complexity?
Time Complexity is a measure of how an algorithm's runtime increases as the input size n increases. We ignore the hardware and software and just count the number of operations.

ğŸ“ 2. Order of Time Complexities
Hereâ€™s a ranking of common time complexities from best to worst (for performance):

Big-O Notation	Name	Order of Growth	Performance
O(1)	Constant	1	ğŸ”¥ Fastest (Best)
O(log n)	Logarithmic	Slows down quickly	ğŸš€ Very Fast
O(n)	Linear	Increases directly with n	âœ… Acceptable
O(n log n)	Linearithmic	Slightly more than linear	âš ï¸ Efficient
O(nÂ²)	Quadratic	Squared growth	ğŸ¢ Slow
O(nÂ³)	Cubic	Cubed growth	ğŸŒ Slower
O(2â¿)	Exponential	Explodes fast	âŒ Unusable
O(n!)	Factorial	Worst case ever	ğŸ’€ Extremely Slow

